ng%20a%20smartphone%20for%20their%20son%20(not%20pictured).%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20preteen%20feels%20left%20out%20because%20he's%20one%20of%20the%20few%20kids%20in%20his%20class%20without%20a%20cellphone.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20concerned%20he%20lacks%20the%20impulse%20control%20for%20a%20phone%20or%20smartwatch.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWe%20decided%20against%20getting%20him%20one%20for%20now%2C%20but%20will%20keep%20an%20open%20conversation%20about%20the%20topic.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMy%2012-year-old%20feels%20left%20out%20at%20school%20because%20he's%20not%20in%20a%20group%20chat%20with%20his%20classmates.%20He%20says%20he's%20one%20of%20the%20only%20kids%20in%20his%20class%20without%20a%20phone%20or%20smartwatch.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.commonsensemedia.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fresearch%2Freport%2F8-18-census-integrated-report-final-web_0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECommon%20Sense%20Media%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%2071%25%20of%2012-year-olds%20had%20their%20own%20smartphone%20as%20of%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20want%20my%20son%20to%20feel%20left%20out.%20However%2C%20he%20already%20owns%20a%20Nintendo%20Switch%2C%20a%20Kindle%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fipad-kid-generation-tips-reduce-screen-time-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20iPad%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20with%20strict%20screen%20usage%20limits%2C%20his%20access%20to%20the%20digital%20world%20feels%20robust%20enough%20for%20his%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20kitchen%20table%20a%20few%20nights%20ago%2C%20my%20son%20wrote%20a%20persuasive%20essay%20about%20why%20he%20should%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fipad-kids-tiktokers-worried-gen-z-millennials-gen-alpha-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epermitted%20a%20smartwatch%20or%20a%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20well-researched%2C%20including%20this%20zinger%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20only%20need%20to%20use%20it%20when%20I%20go%20out%20with%20friends%2C%20so%20you%20don't%20worry%20about%20me.%20I%20can%20leave%20it%20on%20the%20charger%20when%20I'm%20at%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20sounds%20innocent%20enough%20%E2%80%94%20a%20tool%20that%20will%20keep%20him%20in%20contact%20with%20us%20when%20he%20isn't%20home.%20However%2C%20I%20doubt%20the%20device%20will%20live%20on%20the%20charger.%20I've%20heard%20from%20other%20parents%20whose%20preteens%20are%20in%20the%20school%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmodern-etiquette-guide-for-group-chats-better-social-media-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egroup%20chat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20the%20messages%20come%20in%20fast%20succession%20and%20often%20at%20odd%20hours.%20With%20access%2C%20my%20son%20will%20likely%20obsess%20over%20the%20influx%20of%20messages%2C%20making%20his%20emotional%20attachments%20to%20friends%20even%20more%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2291f88912-3d5d-4a33-bd7d-f3f393b8bfd4%5C%22%3EI%20worry%20about%20the%20consequences%20of%20getting%20him%20a%20phone%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20preteens%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgave-kids-cellpohones-early-after-my-divorce-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephone%20or%20other%20tech%20device%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20has%20more%20consequences%20than%20only%20staying%20connected%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrkyrabobinet.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Kyra%20Bobinet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20physician%20and%20behavioral%20expert%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Because%20the%20prefrontal%20cortex%2C%20which%20manages%20impulse%20control%20and%20decision-making%2C%20is%20still%20developing%2C%20%26quot%3Bintroducing%20phones%20too%20early%20may%20overwhelm%20a%20preteen%20with%20constant%20notifications%20and%20endless%20online%20options%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20them%20to%20self-regulate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20These%20distractions%20can%20make%20it%20hard%20for%20them%20to%20form%20boundaries%20around%20screens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20preteen%20already%20melts%20down%20when%20his%20timer%20rings%20to%20turn%20off%20his%20devices%2C%20and%20he%20sometimes%20attempts%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-struggle-managing-kids-screen-time-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esneak%20more%20screen%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20my%20experience%2C%20he%20lacks%20the%20impulse%20control%20and%20self-constraint%20for%20a%20cellphone%20or%20smartwatch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mindpath.com%2Fstaff%2Fzishan-khan-md%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Zishan%20Khan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20child%2C%20adolescent%2C%20and%20adult%20psychiatrist%2C%20said%20that%20because%20preteens%20(children%20between%20ages%209%20and%2012)%20are%20in%20critical%20stages%20of%20emotional%20and%20cognitive%20development%2C%20devices%20can%20expose%20them%20to%20adult%20content%2C%20peer%20pressure%2C%20and%20social%20media%20dynamics%20they%20aren't%20ready%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-screen-time-expert-limits-kids-screen-time-use-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExcessive%20screen%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20impair%20their%20ability%20to%20focus.%20He%20added%20that%20it%20can%20also%20contribute%20to%20sleep%20disruption%20and%20interfere%20with%20their%20development%20of%20healthy%20coping%20strategies%20and%20positive%20social%20skills.%20Khan%20also%20said%20that%20preteen%20phone%20usage%20comes%20with%20other%20risks%2C%20such%20as%20cyberbullying%20and%20privacy%20and%20safety%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20may%20not%20fully%20understand%20the%20implications%20of%20oversharing%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20whether%20through%20text%2C%20photos%2C%20or%20geolocation%20features%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20never%20ceases%20to%20amaze%20me%20how%20many%20times%20a%20very%20intelligent%2C%20well-meaning%2C%20and%20genuinely%20innocent%20child%20is%20coerced%20into%20doing%20things%20totally%20out%20of%20character%2C%20even%20being%20convinced%20to%20share%20inappropriate%20pictures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmonitor-teen-cellphone-safety-parenting-experts-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreteen%20is%20more%20tech-savvy%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20I%20am.%20Even%20if%20we%20give%20him%20a%20phone%20with%20boundaries%2C%20it's%20possible%20he'd%20outsmart%20our%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22154adc5e-9e6c-4626-8599-73553c3cf7f1%5C%22%3EWhile%20we%20decided%20against%20it%2C%20we're%20keeping%20open%20communication%20about%20the%20issue%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20took%20a%20few%20simple%20steps%20immediately%20following%20our%20son's%20request.%20We%20communicated%20with%20our%20son%20why%20we%20don't%20feel%20he's%20ready%20for%20a%20phone%20or%20smartwatch%2C%20including%20a%20conversation%20about%20his%20current%20behavior%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20told%20him%20that%20we%20don't%20know%20when%20he'll%20get%20a%20device%2C%20and%20we%20also%20assured%20him%20that%20when%20we%20do%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-gave-her-8-year-old-a-cellphone-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20him%20a%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20smartwatch%2C%20we'll%20need%20to%20enforce%20healthy%20boundaries%20and%20restrictions.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20we%20offered%20him%20a%20compromise.%20He%20can%20use%20our%20phones%20to%20text%20friends%20until%20the%20time%20comes%20to%20get%20him%20his%20own%20device.%20We%20also%20promised%20to%20schedule%20intentional%20time%20with%20friends%20outside%20school%20so%20he%20doesn't%20feel%20as%20left%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltho