1a%5C%22%3EI%20don't%20regret%20my%20choice%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20my%2020s%20and%2030s%2C%20I%20was%20figuring%20out%20who%20I%20was%2C%20building%20a%20career%2C%20and%20waiting%20for%20the%20right%20moment.%20For%20me%2C%20that%20moment%20didn't%20come%20until%20I%20was%20almost%2040.%20I%20don't%20regret%20my%20choice%3B%20my%20son%20is%20the%20best%20thing%20that's%20ever%20happened%20to%20me.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20it%20also%20means%20that%20by%20the%20time%20he's%20in%20the%20same%20place%20I%20was%2C%20I%20could%20be%20in%20my%2070s%20or%2080s%20%E2%80%94%20if%20lucky.%20And%20the%20reality%20is%2C%20I%20may%20not%20live%20long%20enough%20to%20see%20him%20become%20a%20father%2C%20let%20alone%20watch%20his%20children%20grow.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20kids%20later%20in%20life%20changes%20how%20you%20think%20about%20time.%20Every%20milestone%20feels%20a%20little%20more%20precious%20because%20you%20know%20you%20might%20not%20have%20as%20many%20of%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20my%20son%20grows%2C%20I%20sometimes%20think%20about%20what%20kind%20of%20person%20he%20will%20become.%20Will%20he%20attend%20college%3F%20What%20career%20path%20will%20he%20choose%3F%20Will%20he%20move%20far%20away%3F%20Will%20he%20find%20someone%20to%20share%20his%20life%20with%2C%20and%20will%20they%20decide%20to%20have%20children%3F%20When%20he's%20starting%20to%20think%20about%20settling%20down%2C%20I'll%20likely%20be%20entering%20my%20senior%20years%20and%20may%20already%20be%20wondering%20how%20much%20time%20I%20have%20left.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e498d9a8-3f6d-4ea3-b1d7-1a210963477e%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20want%20my%20son%20to%20live%20life%20on%20his%20own%20terms%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20not%20something%20I%20think%20about%20often%2C%20but%20when%20I%20do%2C%20it%20hits%20hard.%20The%20idea%20of%20possibly%20not%20becoming%20a%20grandmother%20feels%20bittersweet.%20While%20I%20know%20I'm%20lucky%20to%20have%20the%20family%20I%20do%2C%20there's%20an%20undeniable%20ache%20that%20I%20may%20not%20get%20to%20witness%20my%20family%20grow.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20want%20my%20son%20to%20live%20his%20life%20on%20his%20terms%2C%20to%20take%20the%20time%20he%20needs%20to%20figure%20out%20who%20he%20is%20and%20what%20he%20wants.%20But%20I%20can't%20deny%20the%20pang%20of%20wondering%20whether%20I'll%20get%20to%20see%20him%20as%20a%20dad%20or%20if%20I%20will%20get%20to%20have%20a%20relationship%20with%20my%20potential%20grandchildren.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20truth%20is%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20the%20future%20holds.%20None%20of%20us%20do.%20Maybe%20my%20son%20will%20decide%20to%20have%20children%20earlier%20than%20I%20think%2C%20and%20I'll%20get%20to%20cuddle%20my%20newborn%20grandchildren%20and%20spoil%20them.%20Or%20perhaps%20he%20won't%20want%20kids%20at%20all%2C%20and%20I'll%20need%20to%20let%20go%20of%20that%20dream.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20I%20do%20know%20is%20that%20life%20rarely%20unfolds%20the%20way%20we%20plan.%20The%20best%20I%20can%20do%20is%20cherish%20the%20moments%20I%20have%20now.%20Instead%20of%20focusing%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20ifs%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20try%20to%20be%20present%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20is.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEvery%20laugh%2C%20hug%2C%20milestone%2C%20and%20conversation%20with%20my%20son%20is%20a%20gift.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecame-mom-forties-might-never-be-a-grandma-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734036722000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecame-mom-forties-might-never-be-a-grandma-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20was%20more%20emotionally%20mature%20by%20the%20time%20I%20became