ntinas-javier-mileis-fiscal-reforms-inspire-musk-and-ramaswamys-doge-agenda%2Famp_articleshow%2F116261499.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ffrom-buenos-aires-to-washington-can-argentinas-javier-mileis-fiscal-reforms-inspire-musk-and-ramaswamys-doge-agenda%2Famp_articleshow%2F116261499.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kurdish-led%20Syria%20force%20'critical'%20to%20blocking%20IS%20resurgence%3A%20Blinken%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734024455000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-116262275%2Cimgsize-58594.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fkurdish-led-syria-force-critical-to-blocking-is-resurgence-blinken%2Farticleshow%2F116262242.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F116262242.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EDuring%20a%20visit%20to%20Jordan%2C%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20emphasized%20the%20Syrian%20Democratic%20Forces'%20(SDF)%20crucial%20role%20in%20preventing%20the%20resurgence%20of%20ISIS%20in%20Syria.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fkurdish-led-syria-force-critical-to-blocking-is-resurgence-blinken%2Farticleshow%2F116262242.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fkurdish-led-syria-force-critical-to-blocking-is-resurgence-blinken%2Famp_articleshow%2F116262242.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fkurdish-led-syria-force-critical-to-blocking-is-resurgence-blinken%2Famp_articleshow%2F116262242.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20India%20Revisits%20'One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election'%2C%207%20Other%20Countries%20Play%20A%20Part%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia%20aims%20to%20move%20to%20a%20system%20of%20holding%20a%20singular%2C%20unified%2C%20gargantuan%20election%20in%20which%20citizens%20elect%20both%20the%20Central%20government%20and%20respective%20state%20(federal)%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20not%20be%20the%20first%20time%20India%20attempts%20this%20system%20of%20election.%20When%20the%20country%20earned%20its%20Independence%20in%201947%2C%20the%20founding%20fathers%20had%20planned%20for%20this%20very%20model%20of%20election%20-%20simultaneous%20parliamentary%20and%20state%20assembly%20polls.%20From%20the%20very%20first%20election%20held%20in%20the%20country%20-%20in%201952%20-%20this%20was%20the%20way%20India%20voted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20all%20that%20changed%20in%201967%20-%20when%20India%20voted%20for%20the%20last%20time%20under%20the%20'One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election'%20format.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20all%20of%20India%20voted%20in%20a%20single%20phase%2C%20except%20for%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20(formerly%20United%20Provinces)%2C%20which%20voted%20in%20four%20phases.%20Polling%20was%20conducted%20between%20the%2015th%20and%2021st%20of%20February%20that%20year.%20This%20was%20India's%20fourth%20such%20election%20and%20polling%20was%20carried%20out%20to%20elect%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20to%20520%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20and%203%2C563%20Assembly%20constituencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20era%20of%20coalition%20politics%20peaked%2C%20and%20ultimately%20led%20to%20the%20end%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20in%20the%20country.%20Till%201967%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20the%20only%20party%20which%20governed%20India%2C%20but%20by%20then%20it%20was%20facing%20several%20challenges%20and%20setbacks.%20India's%20first%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20had%20died%20a%20few%20year%20ago%2C%20his%20daughter%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%20was%20facing%20pressure%20from%20key%20allies%3B%20the%20Congress%20was%20facing%20large-scale%20anti-incumbency%20as%20well%20as%20struggling%20with%20an%20internal%20power%20tussle%2C%20and%20to%20top%20it%20all%2C%20India%20had%20lost%20the%201962%20war%20against%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESix%20decades%20hence%2C%20India%20now%20looks%20to%20resume%20the%20'One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election'.%20The%20Union%20Cabinet%20led%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20has%20cleared%20the%20proposal%20and%20approved%20the%20bills%20to%20implement%20it.%20It%20will%20now%20likely%20be%20tabled%20in%20Parliament%20in%20the%20ongoing%20Winter%20Session%2C%20with%20an%20aim%20to%20be%20passed%20Constitutionally%20for%20it%20to%20become%20the%20norm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOTHER%20NATIONS%20WITH%20SIMULTANEOUS%20ELECTIONS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20this%20stage%20was%20reached%2C%20a%20high-level%20panel%20had%20been%20formed.%20It%20was%20led%20by%20former%20President%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind.%20The%20panel%20not%20just%20studied%20how%20India%20carried%20out%20such%20elections%20in%20the%20past%20and%20what%20the%20loopholes%20were%20at%20the%20time%2C%20but%20also%20carried%20out%20extensive%20research%20on%20how%20such%20elections%20are%20carried%20out%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20its%20global%20research%2C%20the%20panel%20focused%20on%20seven%20countries%20-%20South%20Africa%2C%20Sweden%2C%20Belgium%2C%20Germany%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20The%20Philippines%2C%20and%20Japan%20-%20all%20of%20which%20carry%20out%20simultaneous%20elections%20and%20have%20been%20doing%20so%20successfully.%20The%20panel%20then%20submitted%20its%20findings%20and%20a%20proposed%20working%20model%20to%20the%20President%20of%20India%2C%20Droupadi%20Murmu%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20report%2C%20the%20panel%20stated%20that%20a%20detailed%20comparative%20analysis%20of%20countries%20with%20similar%20electoral%20processes%20was%20studied%20to%20understand%20their%20workings%20of%20conducting%20simultaneous%20elections.%20The%20aim%20of%20understanding%20multiple%20models%20from%20different%20nations%20carrying%20out%20unified%2C%20simultaneous%20polls%20was%20to%20learn%20and%20adopt%20the%20best%20international%20practices%20and%20to%20ensure%20fairness%20and%20transparency%20in%20the%20electoral%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20South%20Africa%2C%20voters%20cast%20their%20ballots%20for%20both%20the%20National%20Assembly%20and%20Provincial%20Legislatures%20simultaneously.%20However%2C%20municipal%20elections%20are%20held%20separately%20from%20provincial%20ones%20in%20a%20five-year%20cycle%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESweden%2C%20the%20panel%20stated%2C%20functions%20on%20a%20proportional%20electoral%20system.%20This%20means%20that%20the%20number%20of%20seats%20a%20political%20party%20is%20assigned%20in%20the%20elected%20assembly%20is%20based%20on%20its%20share%20of%20votes%20in%20the%20election.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20a%20system%20where%20elections%20for%20the%20Parliament%20(Riksdag)%2C%20County%20Councils%2C%20and%20Municipal%20Councils%20all%20take%20place%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20These%20elections%20occur%20every%20four%20years%20on%20the%20second%20Sunday%20of%20September%20whereas%20elections%20to%20the%20municipal%20assemblies%20occur%20on%20the%20second%20Sunday%20of%20September%2C%20once%20every%20five%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20also%20studied%20the%20German%20model%20of%20electioneering.%20In%20its%20report%20is%20stated%20that%20in%20Germany%2C%20there%20is%20a%20constructive%20vote%20of%20no-confidence%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20procedure%20for%20the%20appointment%20of%20a%20Chancellor%20made%20by%20the%20Bundestag%20(Germany's%20Lower%20House%20of%20Parliament).%20It%20is%20a%20variation%20on%20the%20motion%20of%20no%20confidence%20that%20allows%20a%20parliament%20to%20withdraw%20confidence%20from%20a%20head%20of%20government%20only%20if%20there%20is%20a%20positive%20majority%20for%20a%20prospective%20successor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Japan%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20is%20firstly%20appointed%20by%20the%20National%20Diet%20and%20thereafter%20accepted%20by%20the%20Emperor.%20According%20to%20the%20report%2C%20a%20key%20member%20in%20the%20high-level%20panel%20had%20suggested%20that%20India%20should%20%26quot%3Badopt%20a%20model%20similar%20to%20that%20in%20Germany%20and%20Japan%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20India%2C%20Indonesia%20also%20switched%20to%20the%20'One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election'%20format%20only%20recently%20-%20in%202019.%20The%20President%2C%20Vice-President%2C%20and%20members%20of%20both%20national%20and%20regional%20legislative%20bodies%20are%20elected%20on%20the%20same%20day.%20According%20to%20the%20report%20by%20the%20high-level%20panel%20%26quot%3BPolitical%20parties%20need%204%20per%20cent%20of%20votes%20to%20qualify%20for%20the%20National%20Parliament.%20A%20Presidential%20candidate%20needs%20more%20than%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20votes%20cast%20overall%20and%20at%20least%2020%20per%20cent%20of%20votes%20in%20more%20than%20half%20the%20country's%20provinces%20to%20win.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3BOn%20February%2014%2C%202024%2C%20Indonesia%20successfully%20conducted%20simultaneous%20elections.%20It%20was%20termed%20as%20the%20world's%20largest%20single%20day%20elections%20since%20nearly%20200%20million%20people%20voted%20across%20all%20five%20levels%20-%20President%2C%20Vice-President%2C%20Members%20of%20Parliament%2C%20Members%20of%20Regional%20Assemblies%20and%20Municipal%20elections.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20a%20country%20of%20more%20than%201.4%20billion%20(1%2C400%20million%20%2F%20140%20crore)%20people%2C%20now%20aims%20to%20create%20the%20world%20record%20by%20conducting%20the%20largest-ever%20simultaneous%20elections.%20Whether%20that%20will%20happen%20in%202029%20is%20not%20certain%20yet.%20It%20will%20first%20have%20to%20pass%20the%20test%20in%20Parliament.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734022860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fv5i53l34_one-nation-one-election-ndtv_625x300_12_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-india-revisits-one-nation-one-election-7-other-countries-play-a-part-7234178%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20aims%20to%20move%20to%20a%20system%20of%20holding%20a%20singular%2C%20unified%2C%20gargantuan%20election%20in%20which%20citizens%20elect%20both%20the%20Central%20government%20and%20respective%20state%20(federal)%20governments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sterlite%20Power%20raises%20Rs%20725%20crore%20to%20fuel%20GPS%20business%20expansion%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734022814000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsterlite-power-raises-rs-725-crore-from-gef-capital-enam-holdings-124121201048_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fund%20to%20fuel%20expansion%20plan%20of%20recently%20hived-off%20GPS%20business%20of%20company%3A%20MD%20Pratik%20Agarwal%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsterlite-power-raises-rs-725-crore-from-gef-capital-enam-holdings-124121201048_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Anything%20can%20happen'%3A%20Donald%20Trump%20on%20possibility%20of%20war%20with%20Iran%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734022512000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-116261759%2Cimgsize-851092.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fanything-can-happen-donald-trump-on-possibility-of-war-with-iran%2Farticleshow%2F116261674.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%2